description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NHS Professionals in partnership with University Hospital Plymouth NHS Trust are looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Occupational Health and Wellbeing Nurse Advisors&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;to join the bank.  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Flexible and long term opportunities are available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location – Derriford Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay rate –     Day rate:                                           £16.97 per hour &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;paid weekly&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;                        Night/Saturday rate:                      £22.06 per hour &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;paid weekly&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sunday/Bank Holiday rate:          £27.15 per hour &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;paid weekly&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;            &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NHS Professionals is the leading provider of managed flexible workforce services to the NHS with approximately 40,000 nurses, doctors, administration and clerical and other healthcare professionals signed to its bank. We help our 62 NHS Trust clients implement tactical measures to improve workforce efficiency and productivity as part of an overall workforce strategy&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking Occupational Health and Wellbeing Nurse Advisorswho are motivated and enthusiastic with excellent communication and team working skills to join our bank. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to apply for this post you must have a minimum of 6 months’ experience in a similar role held within the last 2 years, and hold NMC Registered Nurse qualification and a valid PIN. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post holder should be able:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable post registration general nursing as well &lt;strong&gt;as recent occupational health nursing experience preferably within one or more of the following sectors: NHS, the Public sector, private OH sector, or an Industry setting.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience/knowledge of undertaking &lt;strong&gt;health surveillance such as audiometry, spirometry, HAVS etc., and undertaking medicals such as forklift truck, working at height and confined space etc&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience/knowledge of Health and Safety, risk assessment, clinical audit, research, evidence based practice within clinical setting and policy/procedural development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience/knowledge of Immunisation and Screening for healthcare workers and workers at risk of occupational disease.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Up to date awareness and understanding of the NHS strategy and agenda, national directives, other DoH, CQC and HSE legislation, SEQOHS and all governance aspects, specifically related to work, health and well-being.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable experience of IT systems including e-mail, Word, Excel etc. with speed and accuracy of computer skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence of meeting regulatory (i.e. recent and relevant) CPD/Revalidation requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work and your professional, caring and reliable service you will have access to the following benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Competitive, weekly pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Paid annual leave&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Training and development opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Access to our very own pension’s scheme called ‘NHSP Stakeholder pension’&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Access to a wealth of Health Service Discounts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that you will be contacted via email throughout the recruitment process, so please check your emails regularly.&lt;/p&gt;
